Yesterday the world lost an incredible and talented woman. She wasn’t just a director and choreographer, she was my friend. She pushed me, inspired me, believed in me, encouraged me, and our last conversation she told me how proud of me she was and that she would see me soon enough when we do another show together. She cared so much. She was a joy to work with. She made you feel seen. She battled a long fight with cancer and although this past year was difficult with her health, she was still doing what she loved whenever she could. Peggy, you opened many doors for me in my career and I will always remember that and forever be grateful. I love you and will miss you so much. This is a “boop boop change” as she would say, and I will “celebrate my lunch” for her. The theatre world (Broadway and Regional) along with the Film and Dance world won’t be the same without her and will forever be impacted with the lives she touched and everything she created. The video was when we first worked together in Gentleman’s Guide to Love and Murder with @3dtheatricals

Honestly this went as expected 😂 She loves certain characters on tv and from afar first and then needs time to warm up to them in person. She will let me know when she’s ready. 🥰 I just love how excited she gets to see Spiderman. 🕸️ 🕷️

This MOVIE. I can’t wait for you all to see it. @marvel and @jamesgunn created such a stellar film that ties together the trilogy and gives you closure, all the feels, laughs, and TEARS. My gosh. Happy 20th Wicked 💚💗 It was on October 30th but I’ve been busy. 🙃 This musical changed everything for me. I was in musical theatre class in highschool and our teacher let us listen to it. I heard @idinamenzel ‘s voice and I was immediately inspired. I grew up on Rogers and Hammerstein type shows and wanted to be a more classic sounding soprano, but not after that album. I could hit those notes, but I remember saying “I wanna sing them like THAT” and then I went on to self teach myself how to mix belt and make a career out of it. From then on, I wanted to be in pop and rock musicals and it’s where I’ve found my place in the theatre world. Thank you Wicked. You changed me for good. 🥹💚 Absolutely love these photos by @ericcarrollphoto and edits by @janebergstrom Galinda: @tory.hatcher #wicked #wickedmusical #broadway #elphaba #glinda #oz #musical #musicaltheatre #theatre

💙Holiday Harmony💙 When I made the decision to return for caroling season this year I had anxiety and sadness because I knew I would return to a season without so many beautiful and talented people beside me. And I knew I could lose a few of them in my life for choosing to sing with the group despite false rumors and choosing to support and stand by a dear friend of mine. All that simply to say this season has been beautiful and special in its own way. I may have lost a few, but I gained so many wonderfully kind and beautiful souls in my life. We are halfway through the season and I don’t want it to end. Grateful for all pictured and those that aren’t. 💙
